Creating Vtabs — Step by Step

1. Define your elements as a filter. Vtabs uses `[subfilter<elements>]`, so pass a filter that returns your element list. For a static list: `"alpha beta gamma"` works (treated as a title list). For dynamic: `"[tag[MyTag]sort[title]]"`.

2. Define the type function. This filter receives `<<element>>` and returns a type code. Use `~` (else) chains with `prefix[]then[]` or `match[]then[]` patterns.

3. Provide `$fill` slots for each type you use. At minimum, provide `view-sec` for section headers and the relevant type slots.

4. Set `state` explicitly if you need to read `<state>:last-click` or check collapse state externally.

Minimal example (sections + actions):

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs"
  elements="settings item-1 item-2 item-3"
  type-fn="[<element>match[settings]then[sec]else[act]]"
  state="$:/state/demo/vtabs">

  <$fill $name="view-sec">
    <strong><<element>></strong>
  </$fill>

  <$fill $name="view-act">
    &#9654; <<element>>
  </$fill>
</$transclude>

Last clicked: <$text text={{$:/state/demo/vtabs:last-click}}/>
```

With links and subcomponents:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs"
  elements="nav home about contact tags"
  type-fn="[<element>match[nav]then[sec]]~[<element>match[tags]then[sco]]~[[lnk]]"
  state="$:/state/demo/vtabs-full">

  <$fill $name="view-sec">
    <strong>&#9776; <<element>></strong>
  </$fill>

  <$fill $name="view-lnk">
    &#128279; <<element>>
  </$fill>

  <$fill $name="view-sco">
    <$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
      elements="Tag1 Tag2 Tag3"
      selection="multi"
      state=`$:/state/demo/vtabs-full:$(element)$`/>
  </$fill>
</$transclude>
```

Dynamic elements from wiki data:

```
<$let my-elements={{{[tag[NavItem]sort[order]join[ ]]}}}>
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs"
  elements=<<my-elements>>
  type-fn="[<element>get[nav-type]]"
  state="$:/state/demo/vtabs-dynamic">
  ...slots...
</$transclude>
</$let>
```

Common patterns:

- **Settings panel**: `sec` for category headers, `act` for individual settings, read `last-click` to show the selected setting's detail view
- **Navigation sidebar**: `sec` for groups, `lnk` for page links, `sco` for nested pill filters
- **Tool palette**: `sec` for tool categories, `act` for tools, `spa` for visual separation between groups

Tips:

- Use `default-collapsed="no"` if you want all sections expanded on load
- The `visible-types` parameter defaults to `"sec"` — add more types if they should remain visible when sections are collapsed (e.g., `visible-types="sec spa"`)
- Subcomponents (`sco`) manage their own state independently — use backtick templates for unique state per element: `state=` `` `$:/state/parent:$(element)$` ``
- Each `sec` element collapses independently — multiple sections in one vtabs each toggle their own children
- If fills contain interactive elements (buttons, popups), wrap them with `class="rrc-no-propagate"` to prevent the row click handler from also firing: `<span class="rrc-no-propagate"><$button>...</$button></span>`
